Thirteen figures representing the rebel angels fall into flames below Christ.  A gowned figure falls below and to the left of Christ.  His body is horizontal with his legs pointed toward the right.  
                  The figure's legs are bent and are only visible to the knee.  His chest is twisted and faces downward with his head turned to the right and slightly upward.  The figure's left arm is bent and his head may rest on his hand or arm; 
                  the sleeve of his garment covers his left hand.  His right arm is not clearly pictured, but perhaps we can see his right forearm, also bent upward.  The figure has curly hair and his mouth is open; he may be howling in fear or pain.  He is likely looking toward Christ.

Thirteen figures representing the rebel angels fall into flames below Christ.  Satan is pictured in the center of the group, eighth from the left.  He is muscular and nude with scales covering his genitals.  Satan falls 
                  upside down and faces out toward the viewer.  His head is bent back and faces down and right in profile.  Both legs are bent to the right; his right foot may touch the left leg of the figure to the right.  His arms are bent and wrap behind his head; 
                  his hands are not visible and are likely positioned behind his head.  His hair is slightly curly.

Eve stands among the roots of the Tree of Knowledge with her legs together and her knees slightly bent.  At least her right foot, and possibly both feet, are on tiptoe.  She is nude with long, slightly curly hair.  Her right arm is bent slightly and holds the body of a 
                     serpent around her hips.  She is bound by the snake, at least in part, and looks to its head.  Her left arm is bent upwards and she cradles the head of the serpent in her left hand.  She bends to the right at her waist towards the serpent and turns her head to the right to look at the serpent.  Eve's mouth is open with upper teeth visible; 
                     she takes and eats the fruit directly from the serpent's mouth in an eroticized parody of her kiss with Adam in the fourth illustration.
